def: One skilled in pharmacy; a druggist. See the Note underApothecary.

Situated or occurring within an inclosure; shut off from publicsight; private; secluded; retired.I have no Turkish proclivities, and I do not think that, after all,impaling is preferable as a mode of capital punishment tointraparietal hanging. Roll
Affected with madness; raging; furious.-- Mad"ding*ly, adv. [Archaic]Far from the madding crowd's ignoble strife. Gray.The madding wheels Of brazen chariots raged. Milton.
Pertaining to, or containing, gonidia or gonimia, as that partof a lichen which contains the green or chlorophyll-bearing cells.
To make Russian, or more or less like the Russians; as, toRussianize the Poles.
Characterized by containing the rudiments of both flowers andleaves; -- applied to a bud.
An abandoned person; one openly and shamelessly vicious; adissolute person. "Such a profligate as Antony." Swift.
The person to whom a grant or conveyance is made.His grace will not survive the poor grantee he despises. Burke.
